---
title: Rajas Quesadillas All In One Pan
description: As we’ve grown more sophisticated in this life, so have our quesadillas. Gone are the days of the microwaved renditions of our youth (they got the job done, but they definitely weren’t delicious). This real-deal quesadilla is packed with a cilantro-laden jumble of poblano, onion, and tomato, plus two kinds of gooey, melty cheese. On top, there’s guacamole, fresh salsa, and a drizzle of spiced crema. A good thing just got a whole lot better.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/rajas-quesadillas-1e150959.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/rajas-quesadillas-5e503a4c1309dc11e5316517-d21c0f49.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 680 kcal
  fat: 40 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1130 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/rajas-quesadillas-5e503a4c1309dc11e5316517
servings: 2
cuisine: Mexican
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @Poblano Pepper{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP. Dice @Roma Tomato{2}. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @Lime{1}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Mince a few slices of onion until you have 4 TBSP.

In a #small bowl{}, combine minced onion, half the tomatoes, half the cilantro, and juice from half the lime. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine half the @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon} and @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use ½ tsp Southwest Spice.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano, sliced onion, and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Stir in remaining tomatoes, remaining Southwest Spice, and 2 TBSP water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are softened and mixture is thickened and saucy.

Remove from heat; stir in remaining cilantro and sour cream. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add up to 2 TBSP more water if veggie mixture seems dry.

Place @Flour Tortillas{2} on a clean work surface; sprinkle one half of each tortilla with @Mexican Cheese Blend{1/2%cup}.

Top with veggie filling, then sprinkle with @Pepper Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}.

Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Wash out pan used for veggie filling; return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.

Add quesadillas and cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheeses have melted, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cut quesadillas into wedges. Top with @Guacamole{4%tablespoon} and salsa. Drizzle with crema. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.